recommended:
 I would think that it's a debut work of some third-rate polish or russian developers. It has everything that typical classical polish shooter can offer you:

- terrible dispersion (you can aim right at the enemy's head and bullets will hit anything but the space you are aiming at);
- useless ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s as your allies which are given to you not to help you but to die all the time in the places with most rapid crossfire so you will surely die when trying to resurrect them;
- covering system (I swear I have never seen such a terrible one in any game) you leap to the walls radomly and you can never tell if they will protect you from the shots or not);
- tons of enemies which shoot at you from every corner and whom you can't see through ♥♥♥♥ing gates/grass/trees etc.;
- absolutely ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ story (though I must admit that I liked the characters) and absolutely mocking endings
